Rating: 2
I would actually give this dish closer to 2.5 stars. While it was very nice -with the orange and clove adding interesting and pleasing flavor backdrops - I found the cake's crumb to be a tad too light for my liking (I prefer a moister, slightly denser cake). Next time I might add a dollop of sour cream to the batter and bake for 5 less minutes. All-in-all it was a good cake that went nicely with the recommended sweetened strawberries and cream.

Rating: 2
This was good, the poundcake did not even need strawberries. But there are still better desserts out there.

Rating: 3
I made this for Easter dinner and followed the suggestion of a previous reviewer to use cinnamon whipped cream. My husband loved this (and guests complimented me on it) but I was surprised at how clove-y it was. Next time I think I will try a different spice combination to de-emphasize the cloves. But the cake itself is a great, basic, lighter version of pound cake I'll definitely keep in my repertoire.

