It was okay. I served it to 12 people for dessert on Easter and no one commented on it. It was easy to make though.

Rating: 3
This was delicious,so simple to make and not time consuming at all. I opted for the vanilla ice cream instead of the whipped cream. Guests loved it. Will certainly do it again.

Rating: 4
This is a truly wonderful pound cake. I made it without the glaze and topped it with freshly-made cinnamon whipped cream and sliced berries. The cinnamon brings out the subtle spices in the cake and goes well with strawberries.

Rating: 4
Yummy!! My husband is not a huge fan of cloves so the next time i make this i'll sub cinnamon and nutmeg with just a dash of the cloves. The icing was delicious - this would make an outstanding breakfast bread too.

Rating: 4
A really great recipe. I've made this at least a half dozen times now and use it as a fall back when I want something quick and really good.

Rating: 3
I made this recipe with a few alterations. We were at the cottage for the weekend and I was missing a few ingredients, so I subsitituted Bailey's Irish Cream for the vanilla, fresh lemon peel & juice instead of orange and 1/2 skim and 1/2 10% cream for the milk. It was great and every one raved about it. It would be great with any fresh or stewed fruit.

Rating: 3
A mother's day delight. I followed the recipe exactly and was quite pleased with the results. I debated eliminating the glaze but that extra sweetness was a treat with little effort.

Rating: 3
Definately easy and very tasty. I added Grand Marnier to the cake batter and the strawberries. Buttermilk substituted for milk complemented the essence of orange. I also served the cake with vanilla ice cream instead of sweetened whipped cream. I bet creme fraiche would be yummy as well.

